"""n! means nx(n-1)x...x3x2x1. 
For example, 10!=10x9x...x3x2x1=3628800,
and the sum of the digits in the number 10 is 3+6+2+8+8+0+0=27.
Find the sum of the digits in the number 100!. """

n=100  #n = 100 factorial
product=1
sum=0
for i in range(1,n+1): #to find product that a hundred factorial
    product*=i
product=str(product)  #to get string form of product 
for j  in range(len(product)):  #in for loops, all numbers which belongs to product assigns to "a" variable 
                                # and them sum up into "sum" variable, finally print it.                        
    a=product[j]
    a=int(a)
    sum+=a
print(sum)
